<div class="page-header">
  <h1 class="page-title">Generate COC Certificate</h1>
  <p class="page-subtitle">Activate uncertified overtime credits by issuing certificates</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="card-body" style="text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem;">
    <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <i class="fas fa-certificate" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #cbd5e1; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></i>
    </div>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: #1a1f36; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      Coming in Phase 3
    </h2>

    <p style="color: #697386; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; max-width: 600px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
      This feature will allow HR Staff to generate certificates for uncertified overtime credits.
      Once activated, credits will be available for use and an expiration date will be set.
    </p>

    <div class="info-box" style="text-align: left; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <p style="color: #0c4a6e; font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
        <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>What this feature will do:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 0 1.25rem; padding: 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: #0c4a6e;">
        <li>Select an employee and date range of uncertified overtime</li>
        <li>Preview total hours to be certified</li>
        <li>Generate certificate number (format: COC-YYYY-####)</li>
        <li>Set "Valid Until" date (6 months from certificate date)</li>
        <li>Activate credits and make them available for CTO usage</li>
        <li>Send email notification to employee</li>
        <li>Validate against 120-hour total balance cap</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <button class="btn btn-secondary" disabled>
        <i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Feature Locked
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

